<set entity name=title>Install Agent</set>
<read interform file="heading.inc" process>

<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><th width=340><td><br>
<tr><th align=right>&agentName;:
	<td> Install / <a href="/Agency/remove_agent.if">remove</a> agents
<tr><th><td> <a href="home.if">Home Page</a>
<tr><th><td> <a href="/PIA/Agents/&agentName;/">InterForms</a>
	     (<a href="/My/Agents/&agentName;/">Customized</a>)
</table>
<p>
<hr>

<set entity name="name"><agent-install>&urlQuery;</agent-install></set>
<!-- urlQuery fails because install is normally a POST -->

<if><get entity name="name">
<then>
  <h2>&name; installed:</h2> <p>
  <table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
  <tr><th width=340><td><br>
  <tr><th align=right>&name;:
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;/home.if">home page</a>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;/">index</a>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;/options.if">options</a>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <form action="/Agency/remove_agent.if" method="POST">
	 <input name="agent" value="&name;" type=hidden>
	 <input type="submit" value="Remove &name;">
	 </form>
  </ul>
</then>
<else> <p> Please specify an agent using the form below:
</if>
<p>
<hr>
<h2> Form for installing another agent</a>
<form action="/Agency/install_agent.if" method="POST">
<input type="submit" value="Install">
Name:<input name="agent" value="agent_name" size=30>
Type:<input name="type" value="">
</form>

You can usually leave the <em>type</em> blank and it will default to the name.
If a class-declaration module <code>PIA::Agent::<em>Type</em></code> exists,
it will be loaded if necessary.  The standard ones are in <code><a
href="/PIA/src/lib/perl/PIA/Agent/"
>/PIA/src/lib/perl/PIA/Agent/</a></code><p>


  
  
